com.usebottles.bottles (2021.8.14-treviso) precise; urgency=low

  * Toggle the last Update date in the bottles list
  * Fallback the working directory to the executable path if it fails to run
  * Now a visual feedback is provided when a download fail the checksum validation
  * Wine support for Wayland trought XWayland
  * Support for 32-bit bottles with custom environment
  * Removed colors from the environments in the bottle creation as these can be interpreted as suggested actions
  * Now the user can only install one dependency per time to avoid conflicts
  * Now the Crash Report dialog display similar reports before send a new one
  * Now it is possible to clone a bottle with a new name, this can also be used for bottles templating
  * The Bottles version is now provided in the Crash report
  * Reduced the Flatpak permissions
  * You can now choose a custom working directory for each bottle
  * You can see a new button in the bottle details with a folder icon, this helps you expose new directories to Bottles
  * Fixed a bug in the detection of broken bottles
  * Fixed a bug that was causing a File Not Found error with broken downloads
  * Fixed a bug that make Bottles crash when the user goes offline during a download
  * Same as the above but this handle downloads with wrong sizes than the source
  * Fixed the File Manager integration in Flatpak
  * Fixed a bug that make Bottles crash when fail in name resolution during a download
  * Fixed a bug in temp directory clean up
  * Fixed a bug that make Bottles crash when the Update Date is not set in the bottle
  * Fixed a bug in bottle configuration upgrade that was causing a loop
